1.General Provisions

This privacy policy was originally drafted in Russian. The English version is provided solely for the convenience of Users. In the event of any contradictions or discrepancies between the versions, the original Russian version shall take exclusive legal precedence.
Project Name: Luna
Project Essence: Public discord bot
Project Owner: YunoSL
Contact Information: Github:https://github.com/YunoSL, Email:help.lunabot@gmail.com,
Discord:yuno_sl

By adding the Luna bot to a server or using its commands, you confirm that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and consent to the processing of data in accordance with it. If you do not agree, do not use the service.

User - The end user of discord using the service

2.What data the service receives

The service collects the following types of data:
1- Unique identifiers (hereinafter IDs): server ids, user ids, text-voice channel ids, message ids
2- Account data: Username, His discriminator, User avatar
3- Server data: Server name, Server avatar, list of members and roles (to the extent necessary for the bot's functions to work)
4-User content: The content of the commands you enter for the bot. (Example: Profile design inside the bot)
5-User uploaded images: graphic files (profile banners) uploaded through the bot functionality. These images are stored and displayed as part of the profile features on a specific server.

3.Use of collected data:

The service uses the collected data to ensure the functionality of the bot
1- Providing bot functionality: Data is needed for the operation of main functions (Moderation, Entertainment commands, Others)
2- Storing settings: The bot uses data to ensure more comfortable use.

4.Data protection:

1- Data storage: Data is stored for as long as necessary for the purposes specified in section 3, or until you withdraw your consent by removing the bot from the server. You can write to our email with a request to delete your data.
2- Storage location: Data is stored in sqlite tables on the secure servers of our hosting provider located in the Russian Federation.
3- Access: Only the project owner has access to the data. We do not transfer data to third parties, except as provided by law, Situations where it is technically necessary for the operation of certain Bot functions (example, accessing third-party APIs).

5.Your rights:
1- You have the right to access: Request information about what your personal data we store.
2- You have the right to demand the deletion of your personal data. Please note that deleting data makes it impossible to use all or part of the Bot's functionality.

6.Terms of changes to the Privacy Policy:
The Project Owner reserves the right to change the terms without notifying the user. The updated version comes into force from the moment of publication. Continued use of the bot after the changes take effect means agreement with them.
